<paragraph blockId="14.[264,1323,1474,1780]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,376,1668,1692]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<typeStatus box="[312,376,1668,1692]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Types</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
: A single specimen in 
<collectionCode box="[627,712,1668,1691]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">MSNM</collectionCode>
: 
<number box="[723,736,1668,1691]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.0">1</number>
ɗ, 
<collectingCountry box="[770,847,1668,1691]" name="Eritrea" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Eritrea</collectingCountry>
: Assab, v­vi. 
<number box="[985,1039,1668,1691]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1907.0">1907</number>
(Katona) lacking both the antennal flagella, both fore legs and both middle legs. Bezzi based the species on only one specimen. Thus, the specimen in 
<collectionCode box="[714,798,1727,1750]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">MSNM</collectionCode>
