<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[264,1323,1815,1882]" lastBlockId="15.[264,1323,284,550]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,378,1815,1841]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks</emphasis>
: Species of 
<taxonomicName box="[525,599,1816,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[525,599,1816,1841]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Geron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can only reliably be identified from the male and, frequently also, the female genitalia. Examination of the genitalia of the unique specimen of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albifacies">
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">G. albifacies</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
showed that 
<taxonomicName box="[491,620,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="michaili">
<emphasis box="[491,620,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">G. michaili</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a synonym. After examination of genitalia of specimens from intermediate localities, Greathead (
<number box="[741,802,324,350]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2001.0">2001</number>
b) showed that Zaitzev’s species from 
<collectingCountry name="Mongolia" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
is present in 
<collectingCountry box="[486,577,364,390]" name="Algeria" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[591,661,364,390]" name="Egypt" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Egypt</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[721,808,364,390]" name="Tunisia" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
as well as Turkmenia and 
<collectingCountry box="[1132,1230,364,390]" name="Ukraine" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[1243,1323,364,390]" name="Eritrea" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Eritrea</collectingCountry>
can now be added to the list.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,284,550]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
It is a small species (ca. 
<quantity box="[597,667,444,470]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
) of the 
<taxonomicName box="[756,892,444,469]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibbosus">
<emphasis box="[756,892,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">G. gibbosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group but with a pale clypeus and is similar in appearance to the even smaller (ca. 2.5– 
<quantity box="[869,938,484,510]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
) 
<taxonomicName authority="Greathead" authorityName="Greathead" box="[957,1233,484,510]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="efflatouni">
<emphasis box="[957,1103,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">G. efflatouni</emphasis>
Greathead
</taxonomicName>
known from 
<collectingCountry box="[328,482,524,550]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[539,630,524,550]" name="Tunisia" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
